node.text:
#ad @target As a Cuban-American in the diaspora, my goal is to remind other hispanic and latino folks about how important it is to stay unified— and to not let where you’re from or your particular flavor or shade, or how you take your coffee, keep you from making connections with people. I’ve never been one to let people decide who I am and who I’m supposed to love… But at the same time I value my traditions so much because they remind me that we have more in common than not. Yes, as people, but especially as Latinx people. 
🇵🇷 🤍 🇨🇺 
Como una Cubana-Americana en la diáspora, mi objetivo es recordarles a ambos hispanos y latinos lo importante que es permanecer unidos, y no dejar que de dónde eres o tu sabor o tono particular, o cómo tomas tu café, le impiden hacer conexiones con la gente. Nunca he dejado que la gente decida quién soy y a quién se supone que debo amar... Pero al mismo tiempo, valoro mucho mis tradiciones porque me recuerdan que tenemos más en común que no. Sí, como personas, pero especialmente como personas Latinxs.  #MasQue

node.text: story time: i skated to this song for the first time in a long time and actually cried so hard (wait til end… nobody else??) and in that very moment, a lil young lady dressed in the perfect shiny blue skate dress approached me to say hi. i didn’t explain why i was wiping tears from my cheeks, but as her mom snapped a pic. of us, grinning ear to ear, i think it will be clear 🥲 they are happy tears
